      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (NIH, RH index) must be directly linked to the clinical decision criterion and regulatory acceptance threshold.",
      "rationale": "The primary QoI is the normalized index of hemolysis, which directly maps to the relative hemolysis index (RH < 1) acceptance criterion. This QoI is the standard metric for blood pump hemolysis assessment per ASTM F1841 and is directly relevant to the clinical consequence of red blood cell damage."
